Here's the context and the connotations I interpreted from:<br>
Respect - Ye can respect (willingness to show consideration i.e. don't step on his toes) someone out of regard/esteem or fear..hehe...here I would say fear...<br>
Command - to deserve and receive as due<br>
(maybe becos he's powerful and fearsome)<br>
<br>
Edit: Forgot to mention that I was thinking of the conversational Chinese interpretation of Rei (pronounced Li)<br>
not the rigid religious Japanese interpretation. Conversational-wise it has many contexts.<br>
